Russia’s attack on Ukraine is continuing, with the capital city of Kyiv targeted. As of Thursday night, 137 were killed and 316 wounded, but there are fears these number will have risen significantly after fresh fighting and bombing over night. Troops have poured in from the Crimean peninsula and assaulted border guards head on along the eastern and northern borders too. There are reports in gun battles in areas around Kyiv and troops are preparing to defend the city amid the sound of air raid sirens. For the latest updates on the Russia-Ukraine war, visit our live blog:  Russia-Ukraine live After the UK government and others announced sanctions yesterday, Moscow banned British flights from its airspace. Meanwhile, more than 1,400 people in Russia were arrested during anti-war demonstrations, with pictures showing them being dragged away by police. Follow Metro.co.uk’s live rolling coverage of the crisis as it happens.